LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
HOUSE JOINT MEMORIAL NO. 8
BY STATE AFFAIRS COMMITTEE
1 A JOINT MEMORIAL
2 TO THE PRESIDENT OF THE UNITED STATES, TO THE MAJORITY AND MINORITY LEADERS
3 OF THE UNITED STATES SENATE, AND TO THE CONGRESSIONAL DELEGATION REPRE-
4 SENTING THE STATE OF IDAHO IN THE CONGRESS OF THE UNITED STATES.
5 We, your Memorialists, the House of Representatives and the Senate of
6 the State of Idaho assembled in the First Regular Session of the Sixty-eighth
7 Idaho Legislature, do hereby respectfully represent that:
8 WHEREAS, Alex J. Adams has served the State of Idaho with distinction in
9 various roles, including as Administrator of the Division of Financial Man-
10 agement, Director of the Idaho Board of Pharmacy, and most recently as Direc-
11 tor of the Idaho Department of Health and Welfare; and
12 WHEREAS, Mr. Adams has demonstrated a commitment to efficient and re-
13 sponsible government by providing critical leadership in budget management,
14 health care policy, and administrative reform; and
15 WHEREAS, Mr. Adams's work has significantly contributed to greater
16 transparency, innovation, and fiscal responsibility in Idaho state govern-
17 ment; and
18 WHEREAS, Mr. Adams has been recognized for his professional integrity,
19 collaborative leadership style, and deep understanding of both the techni-
20 cal and human aspects of public service; and
21 WHEREAS, Mr. Adams's efforts have significantly benefited Idaho's cit-
22 izens and have laid the groundwork for Idaho's continued success with re-
23 spect to state operations and governance; and
24 WHEREAS, President Donald J. Trump has nominated Mr. Adams to serve in
25 his administration; and
26 WHEREAS, Mr. Adams's nomination is a testament to his professional ac-
27 complishments and demonstrates the value of Idaho's leadership role on the
28 national stage; and
29 WHEREAS, the United States Senate is charged with the responsibility of
30 providing advice and consent on executive appointments; and
31 WHEREAS, it is in the best interests of the nation to confirm highly ca-
32 pable leaders with a proven record of success.
33 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED by the members of the First Regular Ses-
34 sion of the Sixty-eighth Idaho Legislature, the House of Representatives and
35 the Senate concurring therein, that we hereby commend and honor Alex J. Adams
36 for his exemplary service to the State of Idaho, congratulate him on his nom-
37 ination to President Donald J. Trump's administration, and urge the United
38 States Senate to swiftly approve his nomination.
39 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Chief Clerk of the House of Representa-
40 tives be, and she is hereby authorized and directed to forward a copy of this
41 Memorial to the President of the United States, the majority and minority
42 leaders of the United States Senate, the members of the Idaho congressional
43 delegation, and Alex J. Adams.

